Document: ResourceImporterTextureAtlas
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimportertextureatlas.rst
Summary: Imports textures from PNG images into AtlasTexture or ArrayMesh for 2D animation memory optimization.

This class imports a collection of textures from a PNG image into an AtlasTexture or 2D ArrayMesh. It helps save memory when importing 2D animations from spritesheets. Texture atlases are only supported in 2D rendering, not 3D. See also ResourceImporterTexture and ResourceImporterLayeredTexture.

Note: ResourceImporterTextureAtlas does not handle TileSetAtlasSource, which is created using the TileSet editor instead.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterTextureAtlas  
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimportertextureatlas.rst  
Summary: Properties and their default values for the ResourceImporterTextureAtlas class.  

Property: atlas_file (String): The file path for the atlas. Default: "".  
Property: crop_to_region (bool): Whether to crop textures to their region. Default: false.  
Property: import_mode (int): The mode used for importing the atlas. Default: 0.  
Property: trim_alpha_border_from_region (bool): Whether to trim alpha borders from regions. Default: true.
