Document: ResourceImporterTextureAtlas
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimportertextureatlas.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring texture atlas import behavior, including file path, trimming options, and rendering modes.

atlas_file (String): Path to the atlas spritesheet. Must be set to a valid PNG image path, otherwise the atlas will fail to import. Default: "".

crop_to_region (bool): If true, discards empty areas from the atlas. Only affects final sprite positioning, not storage. Note: Only effective if import_mode is Region. Default: false.

import_mode (int): 0 = Region, 1 = Mesh. Region mode imports as AtlasTexture resource, rendering as a rectangle. May require rendering transparent areas if trimming is ineffective. Mesh mode imports as ArrayMesh, rendering as a polygon. Reduces fill rate for large transparent sprites but may slow rendering if few transparent areas exist. Default: 0.

trim_alpha_border_from_region (bool): If true, trims regions to exclude fully transparent pixels using a clipping rectangle. Saves memory. Note: Only effective if import_mode is Region. Default: true.